{"name": "aldryn-sites", "metadata": {"name": "aldryn-sites", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Framework :: Django", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP"], "home_page": "https://github.com/aldryn/aldryn-sites/", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "An extension for django.contrib.sites, featuring domain redirects and automatic population of the django.contrib.sites.Site table based on settings.", "upload_time": 1543413014}, "documentation": ["# aldryn-sites\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.org/aldryn/aldryn-sites.svg?branch=develop\n:target: https://travis-ci.org/aldryn/aldryn-sites\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/coveralls/aldryn/aldryn-sites.svg\n:target: https://coveralls.io/r/aldryn/aldryn-sites\n```\n\nExtensions to django.contrib.sites.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Domain redirects**: handles smart redirecting to a main domain from alias domains.\n  Taking http/https into consideration.\n- **Site auto-population**: automatically populates the Domain name in `django.contrib.sites.Site.domain` based\n  on the `ALDRYN_SITES_DOMAINS` setting.\n\n## Installation\n\n- add `aldryn_sites` to `INSTALLED_APPS`.\n- add `aldryn_sites.middleware.SiteMiddleware` to `MIDDLEWARE_CLASSES`\n  (place it **before** `djangosecure.middleware.SecurityMiddleware` if redirects should be smart about alias domains\n  possibly not having a valid certificate of their own. The middleware will pick up on `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT` from\n  `django-secure`.)\n\nconfigure `ALDRYN_SITES_DOMAINS`:\n\n```\nALDRYN_SITES_DOMAINS = {\n    1: {  # matches SITE_ID\n        'domain': 'www.example.com',  # main domain that all domains in redirects will redirect to.\n                                      # Auto populates ``django.contrib.sites.Site.domain``\n        'aliases': [                  # these domains will be accessible like the main domain (no redirect).\n            'an.other.domain.com',\n            r'^[a-z0-9-]+\\.anysub\\.com$',  # regexes are supported\n        ],\n        'redirects': [                # these domains will be redirected to the main domain.\n            'example.com',            # add ``'*'`` to redirect all non-main domains to the main one.\n            'example.ch',\n            'www.example.ch',\n            r'^[a-z0-9-]+\\.my-redirect-domain\\.com$',  # regexes are supported\n            r'.*',  # matches any domain (Makes the above rules useless. It's just an example)\n        ],\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWhen using regexes:\n\n- exact matches win over pattern matches\n- pattern redirect matches win over pattern alias matches\n\n## Further Settings\n\nset `ALDRYN_SITES_SET_DOMAIN_NAME` to `False` if you don't want `django.contrib.sites.Site.domain` to be\nauto-populated (default: `True`).\n\n## TODOS\n\n- validate settings\n- test settings validators\n- log warning if there are Sites in the database that are not in the settings\n- pretty display of how redirects will work (in admin and as a simple util)\n- regex support for aliases\n- form to test redirect logic\n- pre-compile and cache regexes\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.module_file", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.metadata", "type": null, "documentation": ["noqa: W605"]}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.models", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__maintainer__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__email__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__url__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__status__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.__doc__", "type": null, "documentation": ["noqa"]}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.default_app_config", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.absolute_import", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.absolute_import", "project": null}}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.unicode_literals", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.unicode_literals", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.conf", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.conf.AldrynSitesConf", "bases": ["AppConf"], "methods": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.conf.AldrynSitesConf.configure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TODO: validate settings"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.conf.AldrynSitesConf.DOMAINS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.conf.AldrynSitesConf.SET_DOMAIN_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.conf.AldrynSitesConf.AUTO_CONFIGURE_ALLOWED_HOSTS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.apps", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.apps.AldrynSitesConfig", "bases": ["AppConfig"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.apps.AldrynSitesConfig.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.apps.AldrynSitesConfig.verbose_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.utils", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.utils.set_site_names", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "force", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.utils.get_redirect_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "current_url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "https", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["priorities are (primary domain and aliases are treated the same):\n\n: exact redirect match > exact alias match > pattern redirect match > pattern alias match\n\n```\nparam current_url\n\nthe url that is being called\n\nparam config\n\nredirect configuration for this url\n\nparam want_https\n\nwhether redirects should go to https (None keeps the current scheme)\n\nreturn\n\nNone for no redirect or an url to redirect to\n```\n"]}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.utils.get_all_domains", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.utils.compile_regexes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pattern_strings", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.utils.match_any", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "patterns", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.utils._has_set_site_names", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.middleware", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.middleware.MiddlewareMixin", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.middleware.SiteMiddleware", "bases": ["MiddlewareMixin"], "methods": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.middleware.SiteMiddleware.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.middleware.SiteMiddleware.process_request", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Redirects any alias domains to the main domain.\n\nTakes into account if SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT (from django-secure) is\nset and redirects directly to the https version of the main domain\nif that is true.\n\nThis middleware must be BEFORE djangosecure.middleware.SecurityMiddleware\nin MIDDLEWARE_CLASSES, so it can prevent the redirect from an alias\ndomain to it's https version by djangosecure.middleware.SecurityMiddleware,\nbecause you might only cover the main domain with the certificate."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "aldryn_sites.tests", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.tests.RedirectOnlyTestingSiteMiddleware", "bases": ["middleware.SiteMiddleware"], "methods": [{"name": "aldryn_sites.tests.RedirectOnlyTestingSiteMiddleware.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "site_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "domains", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name":